What you need to know:

City are seven points clear of fourth-placed Liverpool, with a game in hand, and could kill off any hopes of a revival for Jurgen Klopp's men with a first victory at Anfield for 18 yearsAfter a club-record 68-game unbeaten run in the Premier League at Anfield, the Reds have suffered back-to-back 1-0 defeats to Burnley and BrightonAll of the bottom three face tough fixtures this weekend, but failure to win could see the relegation dogfight peter out with a whimper